author: Slidebean
description:
Why immigrant founders often outperform expectations.

Relocating to a new country forces founders to rebuild networks and navigate unfamiliar systems.
But that outsider status also creates clarity, differentiation, and a unique perspective on unmet needs.

When founders stop minimizing their story and start leading with it, perceived disadvantages become strategic assets, particularly in networking and early stage growth.

👉 Visit our YouTube channel for more content.
title: Moving to a new country isn’t a setback, it’s a founder advantage
